To make the soup, heat the olive oil in a saucepan over a medium heat. Add the garlic and leeks and fry 2-3 minutes.Add the chopped bacon and continue to fry for another 3-4 minutes to brown the bacon.Add the cabbage and fry, stirring regularly, for 2-3 minutes, until soft.Add the chicken stock and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.Use a hand-blender to liquidise the soup and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To make the parsley oil, place the chopped parsley and the olive oil in a bowl and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, pour the soup into a warm bowl and drizzle with the parsley oil.